  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 7012.37 sitting directly between the max positive gamma wall at 7000 (+9965.9M) and max negative gamma at 7015 (-2019.8M), dealers are caught in a critical hedging zone where they must buy the current dip given the -1.8%/-3% recent declines. The massive positive gamma wall at 7000 should provide strong support as dealers will aggressively buy any break below this level, while the stacked walls at 7050/7100 create a natural ceiling where dealer selling pressure intensifies. In this PIN regime with 91B+ total GEX, expect violent mean reversion back toward the 7000-7030 range as dealer hedging flows dominate directional momentum.\n\n**Bottom line:** Strong bounce expected back to 7030 as dealers buy this dip aggressively.",
